00:05:10.100 --> 00:05:11.320
of beautiful Sun Valley.

00:05:11.320 --> 00:05:11.820
Idaho.

00:05:11.820 --> 00:05:15.430
So I'm going to show you what's
in my pockets and the reason

00:05:15.430 --> 00:05:19.130
why I came up with this concept
of designing a SCOTTeVEST.

00:05:19.130 --> 00:05:20.960
Well, first and
foremost, I came up

00:05:20.960 --> 00:05:25.110
with this idea of patenting the
concept of wires in clothing,

00:05:25.110 --> 00:05:26.700
because one thing
happened to me.

00:05:26.700 --> 00:05:28.330
It's probably happened
to a lot of you.

00:05:28.330 --> 00:05:31.140
It was pre-iPod days.

00:05:31.140 --> 00:05:32.140
I had a Discman.

00:05:32.140 --> 00:05:33.220
I'm listening to music.

00:05:33.220 --> 00:05:34.750
I got wires dangling
all over me.

00:05:34.750 --> 00:05:36.640
I'm in an airport and
I walk by a doorknob,

00:05:36.640 --> 00:05:39.549
and it practically
pulls off my ear.

00:05:39.549 --> 00:05:40.840
Literally, I grabbed the thing.

00:05:40.840 --> 00:05:42.810
I expected to see
my earlobe on it.

00:05:42.810 --> 00:05:44.550
So I said, there's
got to be a better way

00:05:44.550 --> 00:05:47.470
to design clothing that
incorporates a method

00:05:47.470 --> 00:05:49.350
to wire your devices.

00:05:49.350 --> 00:05:52.650
So I came up with this idea of
incorporating headphone wires,

00:05:52.650 --> 00:05:55.520
but not just headphone
wires but also for batteries

00:05:55.520 --> 00:05:57.880
as well because you want to
keep your devices charged

00:05:57.880 --> 00:05:58.674
at all time.

00:05:58.674 --> 00:06:00.590
And wiring it and routing
it through clothing,

00:06:00.590 --> 00:06:02.437
I filed for a patent
and I got the patent,

00:06:02.437 --> 00:06:03.270
reissued the patent.

00:06:03.270 --> 00:06:05.672
I actually went on "Shark
Tank" to present that company.

00:06:05.672 --> 00:06:08.005
There's a whole back story
to "Shark Tank" if any of you

00:06:08.005 --> 00:06:08.963
have seen that episode.

00:06:08.963 --> 00:06:11.590
It was highly controversial.

00:06:11.590 --> 00:06:14.270
And I actually spent
the first several years

00:06:14.270 --> 00:06:17.080
of the company just thinking,
OK, all I want to do

00:06:17.080 --> 00:06:18.030
is clip coupons.

00:06:18.030 --> 00:06:19.550
I came up with an invention.

00:06:19.550 --> 00:06:21.870
I just wanted license
to other companies.

00:06:21.870 --> 00:06:23.760
I don't want to make anything.

00:06:23.760 --> 00:06:26.910
I just want to collect checks.

00:06:26.910 --> 00:06:29.310
Well, what I found is in the
apparel business especially,

00:06:29.310 --> 00:06:31.440
no one wants to
license a patent.

00:06:31.440 --> 00:06:32.990
They don't believe in patents.

00:06:32.990 --> 00:06:36.500
So I figured, especially the
patent wasn't even issued.

00:06:36.500 --> 00:06:40.650
So I had a patent pending, and
I started SCOTTeVEST merely

00:06:40.650 --> 00:06:42.946
as a proof of
concept back in 2000.

00:06:42.946 --> 00:06:44.070
And a funny thing happened.

00:06:44.070 --> 00:06:47.440
SCOTTeVEST became
wildly successful

00:06:47.440 --> 00:06:50.160
due to what I was doing,
passionate personal promoting,

00:06:50.160 --> 00:06:53.330
because I did not want to
practice law ever again.

00:06:53.330 --> 00:06:56.470
So I took every opportunity
to get out and talk to people.

00:06:56.470 --> 00:06:59.190
You can find me on
blogs back in 2000 just

00:06:59.190 --> 00:07:01.430
interacting with people
trying to get them.

00:07:01.430 --> 00:07:05.300
So without further ado, we have
a pocket here for my cell phone

00:07:05.300 --> 00:07:08.630
that you can actually
see and control right

00:07:08.630 --> 00:07:10.600
